title: For Sale:  Walther P5 Compact VERY RARE!!
postcontent: I have for sale an extremely rare Walther P5 Compact. Very few P5's were imported. And of those only about 8% were the highly desirable Compact. I can only find 2 that have been sold on Armslist nationwide in the last year. And on gun auction sites they normally go for $1300-1700. I know only well educated buyers will want this super collectible firearm. So I hope it goes to a true Walther lover. For such a collectable pistol the price is low enough to actually shoot and carry. And I know the P5 compact is considered to be a super reliable and well built handgun. It was the pistol used by the British and Irish special units. And is also the sidearm of both Connery and Moore as James Bond. This pistol is in 92-97% condition(depending on who you ask). And has all matching number. I can't really see any signs of use. There is no surface scratches or wear marks. By the condition and barrel I would guess it has had less than 100 rounds through it. I do NOT have the box. But I have the owners manual and the mag that it came with. I will only consider face to face transactions in the Worthington/Dublin area.
